# Cloudflare Pages response headers.
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
#
# HSTS: tell browsers to only ever reach this site over HTTPS. The site was
# serving no Strict-Transport-Security header (flagged by the seo-skill crawl).
# 2 years + includeSubDomains. All subdomains are Cloudflare-proxied, so they
# get HTTPS automatically — includeSubDomains is safe.
#
# `preload` is deliberately OMITTED. Adding it and submitting to
# hstspreload.org is near-irreversible and would hard-fail any subdomain that
# ever serves plain HTTP (e.g. a future admin.ascendsystems.ai before its cert
# is live). Add `; preload` and submit only once every subdomain is HTTPS-solid.
/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
